<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,289,458]" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">
This species was described from three females and three males collected in Uttar Pradesh, 
<collectingCountry box="[1175,1236,289,314]" name="India" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">India</collectingCountry>
. According to the original description, it is close to 
<emphasis box="[531,619,325,349]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">
<taxonomicName box="[531,614,325,349]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Azaleothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepidus">lepidus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and belongs to the 
<taxonomicName box="[843,940,325,349]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Azaleothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amabilis">
<emphasis box="[843,940,325,349]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">amabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. Moreover, the authors stated that “it differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[292,373,361,385]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Azaleothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepidus">
<emphasis box="[292,373,361,385]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">lepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having tibiae and three sensoria on antennal segment III”. However, 
<taxonomicName box="[1174,1255,361,385]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Azaleothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="312" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lepidus">
<emphasis box="[1174,1255,361,385]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">lepidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also have tibiae 
<emphasis box="[151,410,397,421]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="312">(as a matter of course)</emphasis>
and three sensoria on the third antennal segment. Unfortunately, the present authors could not find out any more available information for specific determination in the original description.
</paragraph>
